  "response": "Certainly! Here are some definition-based questions that typically have one-word answers:\n\n1. What is a table or collection of comprehensive data or information?\n   - Spreadsheet\n\n2. What is a term for a government by a single person with absolute power?\n   - Tyranny\n\n3. What instrument is used for viewing distant objects in space?\n   - Telescope\n\n4. What do you call a fear of spiders?\n   - Arachnophobia\n\n5. What is the term for a society with no government or ruling authority?\n   - Anarchy\n\n6. What is the word for a playful or humorous imitation?\n   - Parody\n\n7. What do you call writing that forms letters or characters beautifully?\n   - Calligraphy\n\n8. What is the study of human societies and cultures and their development?\n   - Anthropology\n\n9. What name is given to the process of officially joining an organization or institution?\n   - Enrollment\n\n10. What is the term for the killing of a large number of people in a short period of time?\n    - Massacre\n\nThese questions are structured to elicit single-word answers, providing concise definitions.",
